oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Grand Ole Opry Exhibits at Edmond Historical Society
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Exhibitions; Grand Ole Opry (Radio program); Woodcuts (prints);
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Two color window card (blue and red on light yellow) announcing The Grand Ole Opry, a series of exhibits featuring live concerts, film screenings, and programs at the Edmond Historical Society and Museum, during Summer 2006, from June 8 to October 10. Poster features the list of events and a woodcut of a cowboy boot.
